title: Kamran Khan (footballer)
text:
Kamran Khan (born 23 March 1985) is a retired Pakistani <a href="Association%20football">footballer</a>, who throughout his career of 13 years played for <a href="Khan%20Research%20Laboratories%20F.C.">Khan Research Laboratories</a>.
Khan won five <a href="Pakistan%20Premier%20League">league</a> titles and six <a href="National%20Football%20Challenge%20Cup">National Cup</a> with the club.
He was selected for the 2006 <a href="Nepal%20national%20football%20team">Nepal</a> friendlies and the <a href="2006%20AFC%20Challenge%20Cup">2006 AFC Challenge Cup</a> qualifiers where he won his first cap.
